---
  description: Divides the plane into regular hexagons, counts the number of cases in each hexagon, then maps the number of cases to the hexagon fill and convert them with ggplotly.
  function: geom_hex
  permalink: /ggplot2/layers/geoms/geom_hex/
  layout: base
  language: ggplot2
  name: geom_hex
  reference: https://ggplot2.tidyverse.org/reference/
---

# Default hex plot

<pre class="mcode">
d <- ggplot(diamonds, aes(carat, price))
p <-  d + geom_hex()

plotly::ggplotly(p)
</pre>

# Changing size of bins

You can control the size of the bins by specifying the number of bins in each direction.

<pre class="mcode">
d <- ggplot(diamonds, aes(carat, price))
p <-  d + geom_hex(bins = 10)

plotly::ggplotly(p)
</pre>

You can also specify the width of the bins.

<pre class="mcode">
d <- ggplot(diamonds, aes(carat, price))
p <-  d + geom_hex(binwidth = c(1, 1000))

plotly::ggplotly(p)
</pre>
